ss]]\" and \"[[Flatline (Doctor Who)|Flatline]]\", he was credited for both. After appearing in ten episodes (most significantly in \"[[The Caretaker (Doctor Who)|The Caretaker]]\", \"[[In the Forest of the Night]]\", \"[[Dark Water (Doctor Who)|Dark Water]]\" and \"[[Death in Heaven]]\"), he died in the pre-credit scene of \"Dark Water\", but he still appeared in the post-credit scenes of the episode, and its follower. The turning point for the finale was when Danny sacrificed himself to save Earth from \"Missy\" ([[The Master (Doctor Who)|the Master]]).</ref> Remi Gooding,<ref>\"[[Listen (Doctor Who)|Listen]]\"</ref> Jeremiah Krage<ref>\"[[Death in Heaven]]\"</ref>)\n*Rigsy ([[Joivan Wade]])<ref>\"[[Flatline (Doctor Who)|Flatline]]\" and \"[[Face the Raven]]\"</ref>\n*Rodrick ([[Paterson Joseph]])<ref name=\"ReferenceC\"/>\n*Lucy Saxon ([[Alexandra Moen]])<ref>Lucy Saxon appears in the [[Tenth Doctor]] episodes \"[[The Sound of Drums]]\", \"[[Last of the Time Lords]]\" and \"[[The End of Time (Doctor Who)|The End of Time]].</ref>\n*[[William Shakespeare]] ([[Hugh Walters (actor)|Hugh Walters]], [[Dean Lennox Kelly]])<ref>William Shakespeare appeared briefly in the [[First Doctor]] serial ''[[The Chase (Doctor Who)|The Chase]]'', and more substantially in the [[Tenth Doctor]] episode \"[[The Shakespeare Code]]\".</ref>\n*Walter Simeon ([[Richard E. Grant]], [[Cameron Strefford]])<ref>Walter Simeon appears in the [[Eleventh Doctor]] episode \"[[The Snowmen]]\". Thereafter, the Great Intelligence assumes Simeon's form and personality (still played by Richard E. Grant) in the [[Eleventh Doctor]] episodes \"[[The Bells of Saint John]]\" and \"[[The Name of the Doctor]]\".</ref>\n*[[Jake Simmonds]] ([[Andrew Hayden-Smith]])<ref>Jake Simmonds appears in the [[Tenth Doctor]] episodes \"[[Rise of the Cybermen]]\", \"[[The Age of Steel]]\", and \"[[Doomsday (Doctor Who)|Doomsday]]\".</ref>\n*[[Luke Smith (The Sarah Jane Adventures)|Luke Smith]] ([[Tommy Knight]])<ref>''[[Th