side Out]]'' || [[Pete Docter]]\n|-\n|''[[Joy (film)|Joy]]'' || [[David O. Russell]]\n|-\n|''[[Sisters (2015 film)|Sisters]]'' || [[Jason Moore (director)|Jason Moore]]\n|-\n|''[[Spy (2015 film)|Spy]]'' || [[Paul Feig]]\n|-\n|''[[Trainwreck (film)|Trainwreck]]'' || [[Judd Apatow]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016|| style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | '''''[[Deadpool (film)|Deadpool]]''''' || style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"| '''[[Tim Miller (director)|Tim Miller]]'''\n|-\n|''[[Central Intelligence]]'' || [[Rawson Marshall Thurber]]\n|-\n|''[[Don't Think Twice]]'' || [[Mike Birbiglia]]\n|-\n|''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]'' || [[Kelly Fremon Craig]]\n|-\n|''[[Hail, Caesar!]]'' || [[Coen brothers|Joel Coen and Ethan Coen]]\n|-\n|''[[The Nice Guys]]'' || [[Shane Black]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2017|| style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | '''''[[The Big Sick]]''''' || style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" |'''[[Michael Showalter]]'''<ref>[https://www.thewrap.com/critics-choice-awards-2018-complete-winners-list/ Critics' Choice Awards 2018: The Complete Winners List - The Wrap]</ref>\n|-\n|''[[The Disaster Artist (film)|The Disaster Artist]]'' || [[James Franco]]\n|-\n|''[[Girls Trip]]'' || [[Malcolm D. Lee]]\n|-\n|''[[I, Tonya]]'' || [[Craig Gillespie]]\n|-\n|''[[Lady Bird (film)|Lady Bird]]''\u00d7\u00b0 || [[Greta Gerwig]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2018 || style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | '''''[[Crazy Rich Asians (film)|Crazy Rich Asians]]''''' || style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" |'''[[Jon M. Chu]]'''<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2019-critics-choice-awards-winners-list-full-1172261 2019 Critics' Choice Awards Winners: List in Full|Hollywood Reporter]</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Deadpool 2]]'' || [[David Leitch (director)|David Leitch]]\n|-\n|''[[The Death of Stalin]]'' || [[Armando Iannucci]]\n|-\n|''[[The Favourite (film)|The Favourite]]''\u00b0 || [[Yorgos Lanthimos]]\n|-\n|''[[Game Night (film)|Game Night]]'' || [[John Francis Daley]] and [[Jonathan Goldstein (filmmaker)|Jonathan Goldstein]]\n|-\n|''[[Sorry to Bother You]]'' || [[Boots Riley]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2019|| style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | '''''[[Dolemite Is My Name]]''''' || style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" |'''[[Craig Brewer]]'''<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-critics-choice-awards-winners-list-full-1267901/item/best-action-movie-critics-choice-award-winners-2020-1268203 2020 Critics' Choice Awards Winners: List in Full|Hollywood Reporter]</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Booksmart]]'' || [[Olivia Wilde]]\n|-\n|''[[The Farewell (2019 film)|The Farewell]]''\u00d7 || [[Lulu Wang (filmmaker)|Lulu Wang]]\n|-\n|''[[Jojo Rabbit]]''\u00b0 || [[Taika Waititi]]\n|-\n|''[[Knives Out]]'' || [[Rian Johnson]]\n|}\n\n{{Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Comedy}}\n{{BFCA Awards Chron}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Broadcast Film Critics Association Awards|F]]\n[[Category:Lists of films by award]]\n[[Category:Awards for best film]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Award given by the  Broadcast Film Critics Association}}\nThe '''Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Comedy''' is one of the awards given to people working in the motion picture industry by the [[Broadcast Film Critics Association]].\n\n==Notes==\n*\u00b0[[Academy Award for Best Picture]] nominee\n*\u00b1[[Academy Award for Best Picture]] winner\n*\u00d7[[Golden Globe Award]] winner\n\n==List of winners and nominees==\n\n===2000s===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"95%\" cellpadding=\"5\"\n|-\n!width=\"100\"|'''Year'''\n!width=\"450\"|'''Winner'''\n!width=\"450\"|'''Director(s)'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2005|| style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | '''''[[The 40-Year-Old Virgin]]'''''||style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | '''[[Judd Apatow]]'''\n|-\n|''[[Kiss Kiss Bang Bang]]'' || [[Shane Black]]\n|-\n|''[[Mrs Henderson Presents]]'' || [[Stephen Frears]]\n|-\n|''[[The Producers (2005 film)|The Producers]]'' || [